The paper discusses a reformulation of the model-checking problem and proposes a new approach to improve verification results, state-space coverage, and performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with formal verification of software, which is a topic that falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the outcomes of model checking, which is a topic that falls under Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE, followed by cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, and cs.LG.
